  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "For everyone that curseth his father or his mother,.... Here begins the account of the penalties annexed to the several laws in the preceding chapter; and that respecting the fear and honour of parents being the first, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 19:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", is here begun with: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "shall surely be put to death; the Targum of Jonathan adds,\"by casting of stones,''stoning being the punishment of such transgressors: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "he hath cursed his father or his mother: to do either is his sin, and a capital crime it is: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "his blood shall be upon him: he shall be guilty of death, be condemned unto it, and punished with it, namely, by stoning; for, as Jarchi observes, wherever it is, \"his blood shall be on him\", or \"their blood shall be on them\", it is to be understood of stoning. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "his blood shall be upon him: he shall be guilty of death, be condemned unto it, and punished with it, namely, by stoning; for, as Jarchi observes, wherever it is, \"his blood shall be on him\", or \"their blood shall be on them\", it is to be understood of stoning. ",
            "children": []
